39:15.497 --> 39:17.580
isolated. And I guess that was the reason they 
dared come in there and take him, because it was off

39:17.600 --> 39:28.511
the line of communication.

39:28.531 --> 39:29.352
Things were... It was interesting at the time. I 
wouldn't want to do it now. It sounds like you've

39:35.258 --> 39:40.847
had a lot of very interesting experiences. Well, 
it was interesting at the time. Of course, I didn't

39:46.356 --> 39:49.982
think about it at the time. It was very foreign to my 
experience because I had grown up while I was

39:50.002 --> 39:58.275
teaching in Los Angeles at the time we met. I had 
never been to Texas or Mexico. I'd gone to New York

40:06.293 --> 40:16.225
and traveled from Los Angeles to New York and 
Virginia and the east, but I'd never been south. So

40:17.627 --> 40:19.469
it was all new to me. I knew no Spanish. So I learned 
my Spanish by the hand and foot method. When you

40:27.140 --> 40:33.368
came to San Antonio, did you make your friends 
among the people that had lived in Mexico? Yes,

40:34.109 --> 40:38.996
many of our friends were people who had lived in 
Mexico. We still have the nucleus of those

40:39.016 --> 40:42.000
friends. There are lots of people in San Antonio 
who have lived in Mexico at one time or another.

40:49.319 --> 40:50.662
still find a new case. And a good many of the, of 
these men who left the mining business about the

40:50.762 --> 41:07.834
same time as Travis did were, some of them settled 
here, and some were in Denver, and he was Why do you

