41:46.404 --> 41:48.887
yes. I can't quite remember.

41:53.674 --> 42:03.349
All the mining interests were taken over by the 
government

41:53.674 --> 42:03.349
because they were German interests. Right. And I 
don't know just how that was... Of course, this

42:07.501 --> 42:21.742
company that Mr. Evans was employed by was the 
American Metals Company, but it was owned by the

42:07.501 --> 42:21.742
German interests, and all the head men who came 
down to the mine were German. But it was taken over

42:23.525 --> 42:26.669
by the government at that time. By the United 
States government? The United States

42:28.952 --> 42:32.057
government, yes. Were there any mining engineers 
from other countries besides the United States

42:32.628 --> 42:40.581
down there? Oh yes, there were very many of them. In 
fact, Mr. Adams' first mine superintendent was an

42:42.825 --> 42:51.619
Englishman, Mr. Gluck. He was an Englishman, but 
he was working for this German company. And we had,

42:57.467 --> 43:02.776
it was, probably had quite a few Germans working 
for them. It was not entirely German. It was,

43:06.562 --> 43:15.395
several of the men I picked up were English, and a 
good many of them were American mining men,

43:06.562 --> 43:15.395
because I can't remember them all. Were any of them 
Italians? No. I don't remember any Italians in the

43:19.061 --> 43:21.545
organization. There were Germans, and there were 
Swiss, What about Mexicans? Were there any

43:26.269 --> 43:32.277
Mexicans in the supervisory positions? Not in the 
head positions. I can't

43:34.139 --> 43:54.306
remember of any of the

43:34.139 --> 43:54.306
officials being Mexicans. Of course, there was a 
large, in Monterey, when we were living down

43:55.585 --> 44:09.641
there, there was a large colony of German settlers 
down there, quite a large group. In fact, they had a

44:09.742 --> 44:13.806
German foreign club.

44:17.711 --> 44:22.977
I remember so distinctly when I, when Mr. Adams had 
this accident over at the mine, And we went to

44:23.767 --> 44:25.769
Monterey. He was in the hospital there. And we were 
moving at that time from one station to another.

44:33.776 --> 44:37.820
And I needed to buy some pajamas. And my Spanish was 
very, very poor. And I went into a men's clothing

44:41.263 --> 44:46.048
firm there in Monterey. And in my very poor 
Spanish, I told him I wanted sleeping garments. I

44:51.553 --> 44:53.655
wanted two-piece sleeping garments. This is a 
very small man that came away on a small stature and

44:53.956 --> 45:03.306
rather a dark complexion. I took him for a Mexican. 
And in my terrible Spanish, I explained what I

45:05.869 --> 45:11.815
wanted, and he answered me in perfect English. And 
he was a Frenchman and president of the foreign

45:13.497 --> 45:17.781
club. And I said, why did you let me struggle along 
with my terrible Spanish? He said, it was such fun

45:23.386 --> 45:25.748
to hear you.

45:30.833 --> 45:36.899
So that was the year we went. After he got out of the 
