46:06.451 --> 46:10.917
know, they couldn't go any place. They had to stay 
right there. I meant to ask, did they actually,

46:13.020 --> 46:19.969
they with their families, live up at the mine, or 
did they live down on their ranches? Oh, no, these

46:20.370 --> 46:24.796
men that worked in the mine lived right there at the 
mine. With their families? Yes, with their

46:26.698 --> 46:28.060
families. And they were, that was their home. They 
had no other home to go to. Of course, I suppose when

46:33.991 --> 46:49.164
the mine closed down, they spread out in the 
country and probably lived with relatives or got

46:33.991 --> 46:49.164
jobs on ranches and wherever they could or went to 
another mine. Of course, there were lots of mines

